abstract: Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez. An Olympic curling coach. A host of ‘Queer Eye.’ At house parties and rallies, stand-ins for the candidates hit the trail in Iowa.
snippet: Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez. An Olympic curling coach. A host of ‘Queer Eye.’ At house parties and rallies, stand-ins for the candidates hit the trail in Iowa.
lead_paragraph: WEST DES MOINES, Iowa — Representative Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez and the filmmaker Michael Moore held a rally in Iowa City for Bernie Sanders. Amy Klobuchar’s daughter, Abigail Bessler, hosted a “Hotdish House Party” in West Des Moines. And Julián Castro, a former presidential candidate himself, hit the campaign trail for Elizabeth Warren.

headline_main: With Senators Stuck in Washington, Surrogates Get Starring Role in Iowa
headline_print_headline: As Senators Return to Washington, Stand-Ins Become Main Attraction in Iowa

abstract: Despite the Trump administration’s effort to persuade Britain to bar the Chinese technology giant from its new broadband network, Boris Johnson decided to grant Huawei limited access.
snippet: Despite the Trump administration’s effort to persuade Britain to bar the Chinese technology giant from its new broadband network, Boris Johnson decided to grant Huawei limited access.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Since becoming Britain’s prime minister six months ago, Boris Johnson has managed to strike a delicate balance in his relationship with President Trump, keeping him at a distance during Britain’s election while more recently showing sympathy for his pressure tactics against Iran.

headline_main: Cipollone calls on senators to ‘end the era of impeachment.’

abstract: Senator Mitch McConnell of Kentucky, the majority leader, drew scattered applause when he made a plea for brevity.
snippet: Senator Mitch McConnell of Kentucky, the majority leader, drew scattered applause when he made a plea for brevity.
lead_paragraph: After less than two hours in the chamber, President Trump’s defense team closed their opening arguments, and the Senate officially adjourned for the day.

abstract: Readers discuss whether enough Republicans will defy their leadership and vote to hear from John Bolton. Also: The New York Civil Liberties Union, on bail reform.
snippet: Readers discuss whether enough Republicans will defy their leadership and vote to hear from John Bolton. Also: The New York Civil Liberties Union, on bail reform.

abstract: Attorney General William Barr ordered federal prosecutors across the U.S. to step up their efforts to combat anti-Semitic hate crimes as he met with Jewish leaders in Brooklyn, New York, on Tuesday.
snippet: Attorney General William Barr ordered federal prosecutors across the U.S. to step up their efforts to combat anti-Semitic hate crimes as he met with Jewish leaders in Brooklyn, New York, on Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Attorney General William Barr ordered federal prosecutors across the U.S. to step up their efforts to combat anti-Semitic hate crimes as he met with Jewish leaders in Brooklyn, New York, on Tuesday.
headline_main: Barr Says There Will Be 'Zero Tolerance' on Anti-Semitism
headline_print_headline: Barr Says There Will Be 'Zero Tolerance' on Anti-Semitism

abstract: Tyrone Abraham served his time. His story shows what happens when a state’s criminal justice system collides with federal immigration enforcement.
snippet: Tyrone Abraham served his time. His story shows what happens when a state’s criminal justice system collides with federal immigration enforcement.
lead_paragraph: Editors’ Note: On Jan. 29, Gov. Andrew Cuomo unconditionally pardoned Mr. Abraham, and the United States Court of Appeals for the Second Circuit granted him an emergency stay of removal.

abstract: Episodic misconduct and ethical lapses among U.S. special operations forces, like the Navy SEALs and Army Green Berets, stem from a culture that puts too much emphasis on fighting and too little on developing good leaders, an in-depth review has concluded.
snippet: Episodic misconduct and ethical lapses among U.S. special operations forces, like the Navy SEALs and Army Green Berets, stem from a culture that puts too much emphasis on fighting and too little on developing good leaders, an in-depth review has c...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Episodic misconduct and ethical lapses among U.S. special operations forces, like the Navy SEALs and Army Green Berets, stem from a culture that puts too much emphasis on fighting and too little on developing good leaders, an in-depth review has concluded.
headline_main: Review Finds Heavy Use of Commando Forces Led to Ethics Slip
headline_print_headline: Review Finds Heavy Use of Commando Forces Led to Ethics Slip

abstract: Lawyers representing U.S. President Donald Trump in his Senate impeachment trial launch a second day of defense arguments on Monday as the proceedings on whether to remove him from office enter a critical week.
snippet: Lawyers representing U.S. President Donald Trump in his Senate impeachment trial launch a second day of defense arguments on Monday as the proceedings on whether to remove him from office enter a critical week.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Lawyers representing U.S. President Donald Trump in his Senate impeachment trial launch a second day of defense arguments on Monday as the proceedings on whether to remove him from office enter a critical week.

abstract: President Donald Trump's lawyers wrapped up their arguments in his impeachment trial on Tuesday with a plea for acquittal, and sought to marginalize former national security adviser John Bolton's explosive allegations as "inadmissible".
